# ============================================================
# 7. CANONICAL DESIGN RULES
# ============================================================

1. Constitution outranks all lower layers.
2. Architecture defines structure, not runtime behavior.
3. Model defines records, not policy.
4. Runtime executes behavior, not authority origin.
5. Flow defines order, not truth ownership.
6. Integration carries approved contracts only.
7. Policy constrains behavior explicitly.
8. Interface must remain explicit.
9. Security must fail closed.
10. Infrastructure supports but does not redefine meaning.
11. Implementation must preserve upper-layer intent.
12. Development must preserve long-term consistency.

# ============================================================
# 8. NO-CONFUSION RULE
# ============================================================

The following confusions are prohibited:

builder vs truth authority
visual vs runtime-hosting
snapshot vs live truth
package vs distribution
distribution vs external-rights
external-rights vs access-license-transfer
integration vs authority origin
operations-support vs governance

# ============================================================
# 9. OFFICIAL POSITION
# ============================================================

PersonaOS is considered structurally valid
only when its documents can be read
through this design map
without contradiction.

